# Reuse Pipeline-Generic as a template (any Xcode repo)

**This repository is the canonical template** (or a fork of it). Prefer **copying infrastructure from here** over keeping a nested `ios-devops-cursor-kit/` folder inside the app repo. Include **`.semgrep/`** with **`.github/`** — **`ios-job-security.yml`** loads those rule files.

## Human + agent entry points

| Situation | File to use |
|-----------|-------------|
| Template files **not** yet in the app; I have a **local path** to Pipeline-Generic and maybe an **empty remote URL** | Root **`CURSOR_IOS_DEVOPS_APPLY_TEMPLATE_PROMPT.txt`** — paste into Agent; fill **TEMPLATE_ROOT** and **TARGET_REMOTE_URL** (or say skip). |
| Workflows already merged into the app; need **discovery + substitutions** + Git | **`CURSOR_IOS_DEVOPS_BOOTSTRAP_PROMPT.txt`** through **`END BOOTSTRAP`**. |
| Routing table, file manifest, “I only have a repo URL” | **`CURSOR_IOS_DEVOPS_REUSE.md`**. |
| Step-by-step copy commands (`rsync`) | **`SETUP_IOS_DEVOPS_KIT.md`**. |

## Repo URL workflow (agent)

- **App clone URL:** If the user wants the pipeline on a repo that is not open yet, **`git clone <url>`** into the workspace (or instruct them to open that clone), then run **apply template** or **bootstrap** from the app root.
- **Empty remote for the app:** When they paste the **HTTPS or SSH URL** of an empty remote, run **`git remote add` / `set-url` + `git push -u`** per **`ios-devops-remote-agent-must-push.mdc`** after commits exist—do not default to a manual-only checklist.

## Legacy kit folder

If **`ios-devops-cursor-kit/`** still exists next to root **`.github/workflows/`**, **delete** the nested kit directory after root files are authoritative—**`SETUP_IOS_DEVOPS_KIT.md`** Step 1 explains why.

## If prompt files are missing

Run **`ios-devops-agent-playbook.mdc`** and **`github-actions-ios-ci.mdc`** with substitutions from **`*.xcodeproj/project.pbxproj`** and shared **`xcshareddata/xcschemes`**.

**Authoritative workflow layout in this template:** orchestrator **`ios.yml`**, reusable jobs **`ios-job-*.yml`**, archive **`ios-release.yml`** — paths and DAG in **`github-actions-ios-ci.mdc`**.
